    <question>
        <prompt>How did Ida B. Wells contribute to civil rights?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">She led the Women's Suffrage Party</option>
            <option letter="b">She documented and fought against lynching</option>
            <option letter="c">She served in Congress</option>
            <option letter="d">She founded a college</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Ida B. Wells was a pioneering investigative journalist who documented and crusaded against lynching, while also fighting for women's rights and co-founding the NAACP.</explanation>
