    <question>
        <prompt>What distinguished Booker T. Washington's approach to racial advancement?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Immediate political confrontation</option>
            <option letter="b">Gradual economic improvement</option>
            <option letter="c">Armed resistance</option>
            <option letter="d">International pressure</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Booker T. Washington advocated for gradual racial advancement through economic self-improvement and industrial education, as outlined in his Atlanta Compromise speech.</explanation>
